snippet: The company reported earnings of $606 million in the June-through-August quarter on Wednesday, up 24 percent from the same period in 2013.
abstract: FedEx reports earnings of $606 million in June-through-August quarter, up 24 percent from same period in 2013; revenue rose 6 percent to $11.7 billion, topping Wall Street forecast of $11.48 billion.
lead_paragraph: The company reported earnings of $606 million in the June-through-August quarter on Wednesday, up 24 percent from the same period in 2013.

headline.main: Earnings at Fedex Soar, Helped by Online Shopping
